#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating Custom Images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "For creating your custom image you need a base &docker; image of &slsa;. You can use any of the pre-built &slsa; images that you can obtain as described in <xref linkend=\"Customizing_Pre-build_Images\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "After you obtain your base &docker; image, you can modify the image by using a <filename>Dockerfile</filename> (usually placed in the build directory). Then use the standard <command>docker</command> building tool to create your custom image:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;docker build <replaceable>PATH_TO_BUILD_DIRECTORY</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "For more information about <literal>docker build</literal> options, see the <link xlink:href=\"https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/commandline/build/\">official Docker documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a &docker; Image for an Application"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid "For information about creating a <filename>Dockerfile</filename> for the application you want to run inside a &docker; container, see <xref linkend=\"docker.dockerizing.application\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Obtaining Base &slsa; Images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "To obtain the base &slsa; images from &suse; registry, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;docker pull registry.suse.com/suse/<replaceable>IMAGENAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, to get the one for &productname; 15, use:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;docker pull registry.suse.com/suse/sle15"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pre-built images do not have repositories configured. But when the &docker; host has a &slea; subscription that provides access to the product used in the image, Zypper will automatically have access to the right repositories."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can customize the &docker; image as described in <xref linkend=\"Customizing_Pre-build_Images\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customizing &slsa; &docker; Images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "The pre-built images do not have any repository configured and do not include any modules or extensions. They contain a <link xlink:href=\"https://github.com/SUSE/container-suseconnect\">zypper service</link> that contacts either the &sccreg; (&scc;) or your &rmtool; (&rmt;) server, according to the configuration of the SLE host that runs the &docker; container. The service obtains the list of repositories available for the product used by the &docker; image. You can also directly declare extensions in your <filename>Dockerfile</filename> (for details refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.docker.sle_images.customizing_the_images.extensions\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid "You do not need to add any credentials to the &docker; image because the machine credentials are automatically injected into the container by the <systemitem class=\"daemon\">docker</systemitem> daemon. They are injected inside of the <literal>/run/secrets</literal> directory. The same applies to the <filename>/etc/SUSEConnect</filename> file of the host system, which is automatically injected into the <filename>/run/secrets</filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credentials and Security"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "The contents of the <filename>/run/secrets</filename> directory are never committed to a &docker; image, hence there is no risk of your credentials leaking."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "To obtain the list of repositories, use the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper ref -s"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "It will automatically add all the repositories to your container. For each repository added to the system a new file will be created under <command>/etc/zypp/repos.d</command> . The URLs of these repositories include an access token that automatically expires after 12 hours. To renew the token call the <command>zypper ref -s</command> command. It is secure to commit these files to a &docker; image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you want to use a different set of credentials, place a custom <filename>/etc/zypp/credentials.d/SCCcredentials</filename> file inside of the &docker; image. It contains the machine credentials that have the subscription you want to use. The same applies to the <filename>SUSEConnect</filename> file: to override the file available on the host system that is running the &docker; container, add a custom <filename>/etc/SUSEConnect</filename> file inside of the &docker; image."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "Now you can create a custom &docker; image by using a <literal>Dockerfile</literal> as described in <xref linkend=\"sec.docker.sle_images.customizing_the_images.sles12\" xrefstyle=\"select:label\"/> and <xref linkend=\"sec.docker.sle_images.customizing_the_images.sles15\" xrefstyle=\"select:label\"/> . In case you would like to move your application to a &docker; container, refer to <xref linkend=\"docker.dockerizing.application\"/> . After you have edited the <filename>Dockerfile</filename> , build the image by running the following command in the same directory in which the <filename>Dockerfile</filename> resides:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;docker build ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Custom &slea;&nbsp;12 Image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following <filename>Dockerfile</filename> creates a simple &docker; image based on &slea;&nbsp;12 SP4:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:159
#, no-c-format
msgid "FROM registry.suse.com/suse/sles12sp4\n"
      "\n"
      "RUN zypper ref -s\n"
      "RUN zypper -n in vim"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:171
#, no-c-format
msgid "FROM registry.suse.com/suse/sles12sp4\n"
      "\n"
      "# Import the crt file of our private SMT server\n"
      "ADD http://smt.test.lan/smt.crt /etc/pki/trust/anchors/smt.crt\n"
      "RUN update-ca-certificates\n"
      "\n"
      "RUN zypper ref -s\n"
      "RUN zypper -n in vim"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Custom &slea;&nbsp;15 Image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following <filename>Dockerfile</filename> creates a simple &docker; image based on &slea;&nbsp;15:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:187
#, no-c-format
msgid "FROM registry.suse.com/suse/sle15\n"
      "\n"
      "RUN zypper ref -s\n"
      "RUN zypper -n in vim"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "When the &docker; host machine is registered against an internal &rmt; server, the &docker; image requires the SSL certificate used by &rmt;: <remark> taroth 2018-08-08: not sure the content of this file is still correct, as SMT has been replaced by RMT (Repository Mirroring Tool) meanwhile - @DEV: please check</remark>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:198
#, no-c-format
msgid "FROM registry.suse.com/suse/sle15\n"
      "\n"
      "# Import the crt file of our private SMT server\n"
      "ADD http://smt.test.lan/smt.crt /etc/pki/trust/anchors/smt.crt\n"
      "RUN update-ca-certificates\n"
      "\n"
      "RUN zypper ref -s\n"
      "RUN zypper -n in vim"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding &slea; Extensions and Modules to Images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid "You may have subscriptions to &slea; extensions or modules that you would like to use in your custom image. To add them to the &docker; image, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: docker_building_images.xml:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Extension and Modules"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add the following into your <filename>Dockerfile</filename> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: docker_building_images.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "ADD *.repo /etc/zypp/repos.d/\n"
      "ADD *.service /etc/zypp/services.d\n"
      "RUN zypper refs &amp;&amp; zypper refresh"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: docker_building_images.xml:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy all <filename>.service</filename> and <filename>.repo</filename> files that you will use into the directory where you will build the &docker; image from the <filename>Dockerfile</filename> ."
msgstr ""

